Basic Outlier treatement¶

Cap Outliers to 2*standard deviation¶

In [197]:
def cap_outliers(array, k=2):
    upper_limit = array.mean() + k*array.std()
    lower_limit = array.mean() - k*array.std()
    array[array<lower_limit] = lower_limit
    array[array>upper_limit] = upper_limit
    return array

# cap outliers in the isted columns

numeric_records = ['Glucose', 'BloodPressure', 'Insulin',
       'BMI', 'DiabetesPedigreeFunction', 'Age']

df_diabetes[numeric_records] = df_diabetes[numeric_records].apply(cap_outliers, axis=0)

We find many parameters to be closely related not a surprise since one parameter affects another or appear together.¶

We deal with this when we do the setup in PYCARET¶

Learnings from EDA¶

1) Data clearly shows a linear relation ship with outcome for Glucose , BMI , Age , Pregnancies and to a lesser extent with blood Pressure. The correlation plot also lists these columns as the top four.

2) Glucose emerges as the most importanct factor. No surprise since diabates is detected confidently only with glucose numbers even in a clinical setting.

3) At Younger Ages even a lesser Glucose Number leads to positive conversions.This Group Can be Targeted Early for intervensions

4) We should probably work towards glucose ranges for different ages groups instead of a single number to identify cases earlier.

The Performance of the model on the unseen data is almost similar to the test/train data sets.¶

Recall - 0.8103¶

Precision - 0.746¶

AUC - 0.8218¶

Accuracy - 0.8247¶

Recall is important in most heathcare models since we need to identify cases with the disease especially if the treatement options even if the disease is not found are harmless in the normal population. We should to try to also try to balance the precision since we cannot have too many False Positives ie people wrongly labelled as diabetics since it burdens the health care system.

The accuracy of this model on unseen data is around 83%

The feature importance plot lists the important features.¶

Linear Regression identifies the important featues which tallies with our eda results. We can confidently say that a linear relationship exists between these Columns and the model chosen finally was also a linear one for classification.¶
